Hi @murong00, the better way to fix this issue may is add type judgment to`GenericJsonRecord`

```
--- a/pulsar-client/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/client/impl/schema/generic/GenericJsonRecord.java
+++ b/pulsar-client/src/main/java/org/apache/pulsar/client/impl/schema/generic/GenericJsonRecord.java
@@ -61,6 +61,8 @@ class GenericJsonRecord extends VersionedGenericRecord {
             return fn.asDouble();
         } else if (fn.isDouble()) {
             return fn.asDouble();
+        } else if (fn.isLong()) {
+            return fn.asLong();
         } else {
             return fn.asText();
         }
```

@Shoothzj 

How do you set up the bookie memory settings? It would be good to share more details about your current set up.

I would also suggest checking out the whitepaper written by Penghui and Devin about a deep-dive into Pulsar Architecture for performance tuning - https://streamnative.io/whitepaper/taking-a-deep-dive-into-apache-pulsar-architecture-for-performance-tuning/
